<section class="inner-sec">
  <div class="sec-eyebrow">How it works in a shop</div>
  <h2>Every channel covered, every client booked</h2>
  <p class="lede">One receptionist handles the phone, the texts, the website, and the socials — and its whole job is getting people onto your books.</p>
  <div class="svc-grid">
    <div class="svc"><strong>Missed-call text-back</strong>A call you can't take instantly becomes a text conversation: "Sorry we missed you — want to grab a time?"</div>
    <div class="svc"><strong>Answers the usuals</strong>Hours, prices, location, each barber's schedule — answered instantly and accurately, any hour.</div>
    <div class="svc"><strong>Straight to your calendar</strong>Clients get sent directly to your real booking page — even the right link for the barber they asked for.</div>
    <div class="svc"><strong>Instagram &amp; Facebook DMs</strong>Every DM answered in minutes with real info and a booking link — not left on read until close.</div>
    <div class="svc"><strong>Website chat</strong>A chat bubble on your site that answers questions and captures the client's name and number.</div>
    <div class="svc"><strong>Human handoff</strong>Anything the AI shouldn't handle gets flagged to your phone with a summary — you jump in when it matters.</div>
  </div>
</section>

